      • Motionprofiler

        public Motionprofiler​(MotionProfile profile,
                      PIDProfile pid_profile,
                      EncoderBase leftEncoder,
                      EncoderBase rightEncoder,
                      double ticks_per_rev,
                      double wheel_diameter,
                      double wheelbaseWidth,
                      java.util.function.DoubleSupplier gyroSupplier)
        Create a MotionProfiler
        Parameters:
        profile - MotionProfile for robot to follow
        pid_profile - PIDProfile defining PID Gains for motion profiling
        leftEncoder - Robot's left drivetrain encoder (as an EncoderBase)
        rightEncoder - Robot's right drivetrain encoder (as an EncoderBase)
        ticks_per_rev - Number of encoder ticks per wheel revolution
        wheel_diameter - Wheel diameter in CM
        wheelbaseWidth - Width of wheelbase in Meters
        gyroSupplier - Method for retrieving gyro angle (This is any method that can return a double, for a NavX, this would be something like: AHRS::getAngle)

    • Method Detail

      • start

        public void start()
        Start the MotionProfiler thread. This will generate the MotionProfile if it nas not yet been generated. WARNING: If not pre-generated, there will be a pause while the robot computes the path. Encoders are also configured here

      • pause

        public void pause()
        Stop the MotionProfiler thread without resetting the followers. This probably should not be used? Has not been fully tested

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stop the MotionProfiler thread, and reset the MotionProfile
